description:
&lt;p&gt;Yeovil District Hospital Health Records department is looking to recruit a motivated, team player to join its busy, dedicated Health Records team, based in our off-site Records Library.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be locating and prepping records for patient hospital attendances and when necessary providing relief cover for the Health Records Couriers who provide a 24/7 service transporting records to and from the Library to Yeovil District Hospital and other NHS Organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The relief courier cover will require working shift rotas to include some evenings and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work can be very physical so a good level of fitness is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the benefits of working for YDH include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working for a Trust voted 1st for Health and Well-being across the UK (NHS staff survey)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full NHS terms and conditions including extensive holidays, Agenda for Change pay with enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounts for local and national retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated well-being services for all employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time position 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Carter, Medical Records &amp; IG Manager Karen.carter@ydh.nhs.uk 01935 384396&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Karen Chorley , Medical Records Supervisor Karen.chorley@ydh.nhs.uk 01935 384961&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
